            
RHEL 7.9 to 8.8 migration 


Please find the attachment for SOP and the leapp packages which are required to upgrade the server.

Please do the pre-requisite for the same on the VM's.
 
1) We required the machines to be updated (i.e. RHEL 7.9) so we can upgrade it to 8.* .
 
2) Need to install “httpd” rpm on the RHEL7.9 and enable the service.
 
3) We required port 9090 enable on source (desktop) to destination (to the server). 
 
4) We required free disk space at least in / 25GB free and in /var, /usr 10GB free.
 
5) “Leapp” rpm needs to be installed on the server.
 
6) mount the RHEL 8.* ISO after the above steps.
 
7) Take Backup/Snapshot of the Server before doing activity.

8) Reboot the System before upgradation to RHEL 8.

Note: Please check with the APP team and if there is database then check with DB also whether they are comfortable with the RHEL 8.*.

link for reference 

https://learningtechnix.wordpress.com/2021/10/18/linux-upgrading-from-redhat-7-to-8/

