==========================================================================

== 1st copy the packages tar file on server ==

tar -xzf Packages.tar.gz -C /rlms/  && rm -rf Packages.tar.gz

mkdir -p /etc/yum.repos.d/backup
mv /etc/yum.repos.d/*.repo /etc/yum.repos.d/backup

touch local2
echo "[local2]" >>  /etc/yum.repos.d/local2.repo
echo "name=local2" >>  /etc/yum.repos.d/local2.repo
echo "baseurl=file:///rlms/Packages" >>  /etc/yum.repos.d/local2.repo
echo "enabled=1" >> /etc/yum.repos.d/local2.repo
echo "gpgcheck=0" >> /etc/yum.repos.d/local2.repo

createrepo /rlms/Packages

yum clean all 
yum repolist all

==========================

yum install httpd* -y
yum install python-urllib3 -y
yum install python-requests* -y
yum install python-enum34* -y
yum install python2-libdnf* -y
yum install python2-libcomps* -y
yum install python2-leapp* -y
yum install python2-hawkey* -y 
yum install libsolv*-y
yum install librhsm* -y
yum install librepo -y
yum install libmodulemd* -y
yum install libdnf* -y
yum install libcomps* -y
yum install leapp-upgrade-* -y
yum install leapp-repository* -y
yum install leapp-deps* -y
yum install leapp-0.15* -y 
yum install cockpit-ws* -y
yum install cockpit-system* -y
yum install cockpit-leapp* -y
yum install cockpit-bridge* -y
yum install cockpit-195* -y

rpm -qa | grep -i leapp
rpm -qa | grep -i cockpit
rpm -qa | grep -i httpd 

systemctl enable --now httpd


mv /etc/yum.repos.d/*.repo /etc/yum.repos.d/backup


=================================================================

now mount iso image of rhel8.8



mkdir /var/www/html/rhel8

mount /rlms/rhel-8.8-x86_64-dvd.iso /var/www/html/rhel8

### mount /dev/sr0 /var/www/html/rhel8

mv /etc/yum.repos.d/*.repo /etc/yum.repos.d/backup

echo "[BaseOS]" >>  /etc/yum.repos.d/local.repo
echo "name=BaseOS" >>  /etc/yum.repos.d/local.repo
echo "baseurl=http://server ip/rhel8/BaseOS " >>  /etc/yum.repos.d/local.repo
echo "enabled=1" >> /etc/yum.repos.d/local.repo
echo "gpgcheck=0" >> /etc/yum.repos.d/local.repo

echo " " >> /etc/yum.repos.d/local.repo

echo " " >> /etc/yum.repos.d/local.repo


echo "[AppStream]" >> /etc/yum.repos.d/local.repo
echo "name=AppStream" >> /etc/yum.repos.d/local.repo
echo "baseurl=http://server ip/rhel8/AppStream" >> /etc/yum.repos.d/local.repo
echo "enabled=1" >> /etc/yum.repos.d/local.repo
echo "gpgcheck=0" >> /etc/yum.repos.d/local.repo


tar -xzf leapp-data-22.tar.gz -C /etc/leapp/files && rm leapp-data-22.tar.gz

leapp preupgrade --no-rhsm --enablerepo BaseOS --enablerepo AppStream


Possible errors which I reported.
1- Direct root login enabled (Disabled the direct root login in the sshd.conf file)
2- Kernel modules unsupported in RHEL8 (Remove the listed kernel modules like modprobe -r <modulename>)
3- There is also one file that is generated i.e. /var/log/leapp/answerfile, 
cat this file it will list the some modules which needs to be removed. 
In my case it was remove_pam_krb5_module_check.confirm, so to remove this module run below command.

leapp answer --section remove_pam_krb5_module_check.confirm=True

Likewise you can remove the modules listed in /var/log/leapp/answerfile.



==========================================================================
4. == error  ==

cat /var/log/leapp/answerfile

(# Title:              None
# Reason:             Confirmation
# =================== remove_pam_pkcs11_module_check.confirm ==================
# Label:              Disable pam_pkcs 11 module in PAM configuration? If no, the upgrade process will be interrupted.
# Description:        PAM module pam_pkcs11 is no longer available in RHEL-8 since it was replaced by SSSD.
# Reason:             Leaving this module in PAM configuration may lock out the system.
# Type:               bool
# Default:            None
# Available choices: True/False
# Unanswered question. Uncomment the following line with your answer
# confirm = 

sulotion = leapp answer --section remove_pam_pkcs11_module_check.confirm=True

======================================================================
5. check inhibitor 

cat  /var/log/leapp/leapp-report.txt |grep -i inhibitor

# rmmod pata_acpi


6- Risk Factor: high (inhibitor)
Title: OpenSSH configured to use removed mac
Summary: OpenSSH is configured to use removed mac hmac-ripemd160. This MAC was removed from OpenSSH and if present the sshd daemon will not start in RHEL 8
Remediation: [hint] Remove the following MACs from sshd_config: hmac-ripemd160
Key: 5e212f4c38746acafd30e981b42b6a61b5802e77

hmac-ripemd160

solution - make changes in sshd file



=====================================================================

4- Once all the issues are resolved, rerun the preupgrade.

leapp preupgrade --no-rhsm --enablerepo BaseOS --enablerepo AppStream

If there are no more errors/issues, then you will see a message “REPORT” or “VIEW REPORT” in green color, this means the system is ready for upgrade.


# leapp upgrade --no-rhsm --enablerepo BaseOS --enablerepo AppStream


6- Once the upgrade is completed, reboot the system.


# reboot

# cat /etc/redhat-release

# uname -r


systemctl enable ds_agent --now

systemctl enable rscd.service --now

systemctl restart splunk

systemctl disable httpd --now

systemctl status httpd

